<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2611759>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Digital images of live animals showing color in life. A. Tritonia nigritigris sp. nov., holotype (LACM 3553), in situ, right side invaginations indicated with arrows. B. Tritonia sp. (SIO-BIC M12395), lab photo. C. Dendronotus claguei sp. nov., holotype (LACM 3555), in situ. D. Ziminella vrijenhoeki sp. nov., holotype (SIO-BIC M12137), lab photo. E. Ziminella vrijenhoeki sp. nov., paratype (SIO-BIC M12135), lab photo. F. Cuthona methana sp. nov., holotype (SIO-BIC M12413), lab photo. G. Cuthona methana sp. nov., paratype (SIO-BIC M12412), lab photo. H. Aeolidia libitinaria sp. nov., holotype (SIO- BIC M12138), lab photo." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2611759/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2611761>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Photographs of the external morphology of preserved specimens of Tritonioidea and Dendronotoidea. A. Holotype of Tritonia nigritigris sp. nov. (LACM 3553), lateral view. B. Paratype of Dendronotus claguei sp. nov. (LACM 3555), lateral view. C–D. Tritonia sp. (SIO-BIC M12395), C. dorsal view of the head, D. lateral view. Abbreviations: a, anus; pe, penis. Arrow indicates damage on the right side of the body." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2611761/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2611763>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Drawings of the internal anatomy of the holotype of Tritonia nigritigris sp. nov. (LACM 3553). A. General view of the internal anatomy. B. Reproductive system. Abbreviations: am, ampulla; bb, buccal bulb; bc, bursa copulatrix; cns, central nervous system; dd, deferent duct; dg, digestive gland; es, esophagus; fgc, female gland complex; ht, heart; i, intestine; pe, penis; pr, prostate; rs, reproductive system; sg, salivary gland; sr, seminal receptacle; vg, vagina." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2611763/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2611765>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. SEMs of the radula and jaws of the holotype of Tritonia nigritigris sp. nov. (LACM 3553). A. Rachidian and inner lateral radular teeth. B. Lateral radular teeth. C. Outer radular teeth. D. Jaw." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2611765/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2611757>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Distribution map of the collection localities in this paper including depth ranges." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2611757/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2611767>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Bayesian consensus phylogenetic analyses of Tritonioidea and Dendronotoidea, with branches collapsed for clarity. The phylogenetic position of the species described herein (in bold) are represented in grey ovals. Posterior probability and maximum likelihood bootstrap values indicated for each branch." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2611767/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

